revenues  parks and resorts revenues increased 1%, or $94 million, to $10.8 billion due to an increase of $132 million at our international operations, partially offset by a decrease of $38 million at our domestic
operations.  the decline in revenue at our domestic operations reflected the impact of one fewer week of operations and a 1%
volume decrease reflecting lower vacation club ownership sales, lower hotel occupancy and lower passenger cruise ship days. these decreases were partially offset by higher guest spending primarily due to higher average ticket prices and higher
average daily hotel room rates.  the 6% revenue increase at our international operations reflected increases of 3% due to
higher guest spending and 3% due to the sale of a real estate property as well as higher attendance and hotel occupancy. higher guest spending was driven by higher average ticket prices and average daily hotel room rates.
