these bank facilities allow for borrowings at libor-based rates plus a spread, which depends on the
companys public debt rating and can range from 0.18% to 4.5%. the company also has the ability to issue up to $800 million of letters of credit under the facility expiring in february 2011, which if utilized, reduces available borrowing under
